						<h2>Cookies</h2>
			<p>To enrich and perfect your online experience, Sacred Traditions, Inc. uses "Cookies", similar technologies and services provided by others to display personalized content, appropriate advertising and store your preferences on your computer.</p>
			<p>A cookie is a string of information that a website stores on a visitor's computer, and that the visitor's browser provides to the website each time the visitor returns. Sacred Traditions, Inc. uses cookies to help Sacred Traditions, Inc. identify and track visitors, their usage of http://sacred-traditions.org, and their website access preferences. Sacred Traditions, Inc. visitors who do not wish to have cookies placed on their computers should set their browsers to refuse cookies before using Sacred Traditions, Inc.'s websites, with the drawback that certain features of Sacred Traditions, Inc.'s websites may not function properly without the aid of cookies.</p>

			<p>By continuing to navigate our website without changing your cookie settings, you hereby acknowledge and agree to Sacred Traditions, Inc.'s use of cookies.</p>

